AETHERMUD STAFF COMMAND: MMSG

SYNTAX
  set MMIN <text with $N>
  set MMOUT <text with $N>
  set MHOME <text with $N>
  unset MMIN | MMOUT | MHOME

DESCRIPTION
  Wizard teleport commands announce your arrival and departure using
  three environment variables. Each must contain the token $N, which
  is replaced with your name (or your race, for players who do not
  know you). If $N is missing, the default message is used instead.

    MMIN   - shown at your DESTINATION when you goto or home there.
             Default: $N appears from the shadows.
    MMOUT  - shown at the room you LEAVE when you goto away.
             Default: $N fades into the shadows.
    MHOME  - shown at the room you LEAVE when you type home.
             Default: $N heads home.

  Use 'set' with no arguments to list your current variables, and
  'unset <VAR>' to return to the default message.

EXAMPLE
  set MMIN $N steps out of a shimmering rift.
  set MMOUT A rift tears open and swallows $N.
  set MHOME $N vanishes in a crack of thunder.

